        <num>30-2-2</num>
        <content>
          <p>The purpose of the industries is to furnish to those citizens of Georgia who are blind or who have not more than 10 percent vision a means of supporting themselves; to furnish an opportunity for those who are mentally gifted to earn a living by working in short shifts as well as to develop their talents for literature, poetry, music, or otherwise; and to furnish a home to workers who desire it.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1937, p. 579, ยง 2; Ga. L. 1982, p. 830, ยง 1.)</p>
